definition: owner/master/host/individual or party concerned/God/Lord/main/to indicate or signify/trump card (in card games)

sentences.english: Her brother is the king, but she is the effective ruler.
sentences.chinese: 她的兄弟是國王，但她纔是實際的主宰者。

sentences.english: I will not be lorded over . " she said to her husband."
sentences.chinese: “我不願受人主宰”，她對她丈夫說。

sentences.english: See who can dominate the world.
The warrant once granted, your will of course directed everything.
sentences.chinese: 逮捕令一旦批了下來，你的意志當然就主宰一切了。

sentences.english: No one nation can or should try to dominate another nation.
sentences.chinese: 沒有哪一個國家能夠或應該試圖主宰另一個國家。

sentences.english: Why did Europe rise to predominance?
sentences.chinese: 爲什麼歐洲會崛起並主宰世界？

sentences.english: Subsequently, browsers produced by Netscape and Microsoft have become predominant.
sentences.chinese: 最後，網景公司和微軟公司的瀏覽器居於主宰地位。

sentences.english: Raziel is officially known as the Chief of the Supreme Mysteries.
sentences.chinese: 拉吉爾是衆所周知最高的神祕主宰。

sentences.english: We know the forth dimension is dominated by the time.
sentences.chinese: 我們知道時間主宰着這第四維。

sentences.english: Fortune reigns in gifts of the world, not in lineament of nature .
sentences.chinese: 命運之神是人世間恩惠的主宰，不能支配自然的相貌。

sentences.english: Like Zoellick, he thinks the dollar will no longer be the dominant currency.
sentences.chinese: 他和佐利克一樣，也認爲美元將不再是主宰型貨幣。

sentences.english: America, Zoellick says, can no longer rely on the dollar ruling the roost.
sentences.chinese: 佐利克表示，美國再也無法依靠美元主宰世界了。

sentences.english: Many people think that information technology and biotechnology will rule the 21st century.
sentences.chinese: 許多人認爲，信息技術和生物工程學將主宰21世紀。

sentences.english: Respondents were quizzed on their feelings about God as a provider of control.
sentences.chinese: 受訪者被問及對主宰萬物的神的感覺。

sentences.english: I live to be the ruler of life, not a slave.
sentences.chinese: 我要做生活的主宰，而非奴隸。

sentences.english: Her skills were in such demand that she could dictate her own salary.
sentences.chinese: 她因其技術奇貨可居，故可以主宰自己的薪金待遇。
